en%20Party%20Alliance%5D.%20I%20spoke%20at%20several%20conferences%20and%20meetings%2C%20wrote%20opinion%20pieces%20in%20Indian%20newspapers%20and%20appeared%20on%20various%20TV%20news%20channels%20to%20speak%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98Peoples%E2%80%99%20Movement%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20ORF%20%5BObserver%20Research%20Foundation%5D%20we%20organised%20a%20meeting%20which%20was%20participated%20by%20M.K.%20Rasgotra%20and%20Professor%20Lok%20Raj%20Baral%20(who%20was%20on%20a%20short%20visit%20to%20India)%20soon%20after%20the%20King%E2%80%99s%20takeover%20in%20February%202005.%20Professor%20Baral%20was%20detained%20and%20harassed%20on%20his%20return%20to%20Nepal%20for%20his%20statement%20at%20the%20ORF%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Nepal%20embassy%20in%20New%20Delhi%20was%20also%20active%20in%20propagating%20the%20legitimacy%20of%20the%20King%E2%80%99s%20coup%20and%20securing%20public%20support%20for%20him.%20I%20participated%20in%20two%20conferences%20organised%20by%20them%2C%20one%20at%20the%20India%20International%20Centre%20(IIC)%20and%20another%20at%20the%20Constitution%20Club.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20327px)%2085vw%2C%20327px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F23152035%2FDabbling-in-Diplomacy_Hi-res.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22327%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F23152035%2FDabbling-in-Diplomacy_Hi-res.jpg%20420w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F23152035%2FDabbling-in-Diplomacy_Hi-res-197x300.jpg%20197w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-698509%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22498%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ES.D.%20Muni%20%3Cem%3EDabbling%20in%20Diplomacy%3C%2Fem%3E%20Konark%20Publishers%20(February%202024)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20IIC%20meeting%2C%20the%20King%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20minister%20Ramesh%20Nath%20Pandey%E2%80%99s%20son%2C%20Nishchal%20Nath%20Pandey%2C%20who%20was%20also%20the%20director%20of%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20Foreign%20Service%20Institute%2C%20vigorously%20pleaded%20that%20the%20King%20would%20be%20able%20to%20finish%20the%20Maoist%20insurgency%20within%20six%20months%20with%20an%20enlarged%20and%20well-equipped%20RNA%20%5BRoyal%20Nepal%20Army%5D.%20I%20strongly%20rebutted%20his%20arguments%20by%20referring%20to%20the%20past%20record%20of%20RNA%20in%20dealing%20with%20the%20Maoists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Constitution%20Club%20meeting%2C%20I%20said%20that%20the%20best%20way%20for%20the%20King%20to%20resolve%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20political%20crisis%20was%20not%20through%20direct%20rule%20but%20abdication%20of%20his%20throne.%20If%20he%20wants%20to%20be%20politically%20relevant%20and%20active%20in%20the%20years%20to%20come%2C%20he%20should%20form%20his%20own%20political%20party%2C%20and%20contest%20elections.%20I%20was%20confident%20that%20he%20will%20win%20popular%20support%20as%20many%20old%20princely%20rulers%20had%20done%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20King%20had%20detained%20all%20the%20major%20political%20party%20leaders%20when%20he%20took%20direct%20control%20of%20the%20government.%20Girija%20Babu%20called%20me%20from%20his%20house%20arrest%20in%20Kathmandu%20asking%20me%20to%20do%20something%20in%20Delhi%20to%20get%20him%20released.%20I%20was%20in%20Mumbai%20for%20my%20periodic%20lecture%20at%20the%20Naval%20War%20College.%20I%20telephoned%20my%20contacts%20in%20MEA%20%5BMinistry%20of%20External%20Affairs%5D%20requesting%20them%20to%20extend%20whatever%20help%20they%20could.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20my%20return%20from%20Mumbai%2C%20I%20was%20invited%20to%20a%20closed-door%20consultation%20meeting%20in%20MEA%20called%20by%20foreign%20minister%20Natwar%20Singh.%20Among%20other%20invitees%20were%20India%E2%80%99s%20former%20ambassadors%20to%20Nepal%2C%20M.K.%20Rasgotra%2C%20K.V.%20Rajan%20and%20Arvind%20Deo.%20Issue%20on%20the%20table%20was%20to%20continue%20or%20not%20the%20pipeline%20of%20arms%20supplies%20to%20the%20King%20after%20his%20takeover.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20most%20of%20the%20other%20participants%20were%20in%20favour%20of%20continuing%20the%20supplies%2C%20I%20and%20Arvind%20Deo%20strongly%20opposed%20it.%20I%20submitted%20that%20the%20King%20will%20use%20these%20arms%20against%20his%20own%20people%20and%20for%20suppressing%20democratic%20movement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20support%20of%20my%20argument%2C%20I%20narrated%20the%20incident%20of%20the%201976%20lunch%20of%20Mrs%20Gandhi%20for%20then%20Prince%20Gyanendra.%20I%20did%20that%20in%20the%20hope%20that%20Mrs%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20reference%2C%20suspecting%20the%20King%E2%80%99s%20democratic%20pretentions%2C%20may%20be%20found%20more%20persuasive%20by%20Natwar%20Singh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20taken%20a%20few%20days%20later%20by%20Government%20of%20India%20was%20to%20stop%20the%20supplies%20and%20force%20the%20King%20to%20make-up%20with%20the%20mainstream%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20studies%20on%20Nepal%2C%20I%20had%20hardly%20any%20contacts%20with%20the%20Royal%20Palace.%20I%20had%20known%20Kumar%20Khadga%20Bikram%20Shah%2C%20the%20son-in-law%20of%20the%20royal%20family%2C%20in%20his%20capacity%20as%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Centre%20for%20Nepal%20and%20Asian%20Studies%20(CNAS)%2C%20Tribhuvan%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20participated%20in%20the%20international%20seminar%20on%20South%20Asian%20Security%20organised%20by%20the%20Centre%20in%201985.%20I%20met%20him%20every%20time%20I%20went%20to%20Kathmandu%20after%20that%20in%20his%20CNAS%20office%20but%20never%20discussed%20Nepali%20politics%20with%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKumar%20Khadga%20Bikram%20Shah%2C%20unfortunately%2C%20got%20killed%20in%20the%20royal%20massacre%20of%202001.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F23155102%2F8581782765_ff3f72e5a6_c.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F23155102%2F8581782765_ff3f72e5a6_c.jpg%20800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F23155102%2F8581782765_ff3f72e5a6_c-300x200.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-698524%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22530%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EKathmandu%E2%80%99s%20Narayanhiti%20Palace%2C%20the%20former%20residence%20of%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20monarchy.%20Photo%3A%20Antoine%2049%2FFlickr.%20CC%20BY%20NC-ND-2.0.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20pursuance%20of%20my%20Nepal%20studies%2C%20on%20a%20couple%20of%20occasions%2C%20I%20had%20interviewed%20the%20then%20personal%20secretary%20to%20King%20Birendra%2C%20Chiran%20Shumshere%20Thapa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20June%202002%2C%20King%20Gyanendra%20visited%20India%20to%20garner%20support%20for%20his%20regime.%20The%20Nepal%20embassy%20in%20New%20Delhi%20organised%20a%20reception%20for%20him.%20I%20met%20the%20King%20in%20that%20reception%20and%20asked%20him%20if%20he%20remembered%20my%20meeting%20him%20at%20Mrs%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20lunch%20in%201976.%20He%20complained%20that%20I%20have%20not%20been%20meeting%20him%20during%20my%20Kathmandu%20visits.%20I%20promised%20to%20do%20so%20next%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20did%20call%20the%20palace%20secretariat%20on%20my%20next%20visit%20to%20Kathmandu%20and%20requested%20for%20an%20audience%20with%20the%20King%2C%20giving%20reference%20to%20the%20exchange%20of%20words%20with%20His%20Majesty%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20The%20office%20assured%20me%20that%20they%20will%20get%20back%20to%20me%2C%20but%20that%20never%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20another%20visit%20to%20Kathmandu%20after%20the%20King%E2%80%99s%20direct%20rule%2C%20former%20foreign%20minister%20Ramesh%20Nath%20Pandey%20invited%20me%20for%20lunch%20at%20his%20residence.%20He%20described%20to%20me%20in%20detail%20how%20he%20succeeded%20in%20securing%20arms%20both%20from%20a%20reluctant%20India%20and%20a%20responsive%20China%20to%20help%20the%20King%20fight%20the%20Maoist%20insurgency.%20Details%20of%20his%20diplomatic%20efforts%20have%20been%20now%20recorded%20in%20his%20memoir%2C%20%3Cem%3EKootniti%20Ra%20Rajniti%3C%2Fem%3E%20(%3Cem%3EDiplomacy%20and%20Politics%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Shangri%20La%20Books%2C%20Kathmandu%2C%202015).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20leaving%20after%20lunch%20and%20discussions%2C%20he%20asked%20me%20for%20a%20favour%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%98Please%20convey%20a%20message%20to%20foreign%20minister%20Natwar%20Singh%20that%20the%20King%20will%20happily%20accommodate%20all%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20economic%20and%20security%20concerns%20in%20return%20for%20support%20to%20his%20domestic%20political%20actions.%E2%80%99%20I%20personally%20conveyed%20this%20message%20as%20desired.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fwill-nepal-pms-upcoming-visit-to-beijing-balance-geopolitical-interests-for-india-and-china%5C%22%3EWill%20Nepal%20PM%E2%80%99s%20Upcoming%20Visit%20to%20Beijing%20Balance%20Geopolitical%20Interests%20for%20India%20and%20China%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20Dr%20Asarfi%20Shah%20used%20to%20meet%20me%20both%20in%20Kathmandu%20and%20New%20Delhi%20to%20seek%20my%20support%20for%20the%20King.%20Once%20in%20Kathmandu%2C%20he%20organised%20a%20special%20worship%20(%3Cem%3Eabhishek%3C%2Fem%3E)%20by%20me%20at%20the%20Lord%20Pashupatinath%20Temple.%20During%20a%20meeting%20in%20my%20IDSA%20%5BInstitute%20for%20Defence%20Studies%20and%20Analyses%5D%20office%2C%20Dr%20Shah%20once%20bragged%20that%20the%20Indian%20establishment%2C%20under%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20regime%2C%20had%20assured%20the%20King%20that%20monarchy%20and%20Hinduism%20represent%20two%20faces%20of%20the%20same%20coin%20that%20India%20would%20support%20in%20Nepal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQuestioning%20the%20need%20for%20additional%20support%2C%20I%20asked%20Dr%20Shah%2C%20%E2%80%98If%20that%20is%20the%20case%2C%20then%20why%20does%20the%20King%20need%20support%20from%20someone%20like%20me%3F%E2%80%99%20It%20is%2C%20however%2C%20not%20in%20my%20DNA%20to%20support%20autocratic%20monarchy.%20I%20made%20this%20stance%20clear%20to%20Dr%20Shah%20on%20every%20occasion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20a%20retired%20R%26amp%3BAW%20%5BResearch%20and%20Analysis%20Wing%5D%20officer%2C%20whom%20I%20knew%20for%20many%20years%20because%20of%20our%20common%20Rajasthani%20origin%2C%20invited%20me%20for%20lunch%20at%20the%20Delhi%20Gymkhana%20Club.%20He%20conveyed%20that%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20chief%20minister%20Yogi%20Adityanath%20was%20keen%20to%20get%20monarchy%20restored%20in%20Nepal%20and%20suggested%20that%20I%20support%20these%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20firmly%20communicated%20that%20he%20had%20approached%20the%20wrong%20person%20for%20a%20wrong%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fs-d-muni%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ES.D.%20Muni%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20Professor%20Emeritus%20at%20JNU%20and%20former%20special%20envoy%20and%20ambassador%2C%20the%20government%20of%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20above%20excerpt%20has%20been%20taken%20with%20permission%20from%20Konark%20Press.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708695034000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F23162317%2FMGY.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmodi-yogi-may-have-supported-nepal-return-to-monarchy-s-d-muni%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'Dr%20Shah%20once%20bragged%20that%20the%20