%20according%20to%20OPM.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.opm.gov%2Fpolicy-data-oversight%2Fpay-leave%2Freference-materials%2Fhandbooks%2Falternative-work-schedules%2F%23Comp%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Ecompressed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20work%20schedule%20(CWS)%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emeans%20that%20an%20employee%20works%20less%20than%2010%20workdays%20during%20a%20two-week%20pay%20period.%20This%20lets%20the%20employee%20work%20more%20hours%20each%20day%20%E2%80%94%20and%20get%20an%20extra%20day%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.opm.gov%2Fpolicy-data-oversight%2Fpay-leave%2Freference-materials%2Fhandbooks%2Falternative-work-schedules%2F%23Flex%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Eflexible%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20work%20schedule%20(FWS)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20consists%20of%20core%20hours%20and%20flexible%20bands.%20%26quot%3BCore%20hours%26quot%3B%20are%20the%20hours%20that%20employees%20have%20to%20be%20present%20during%20work.%20But%20%26quot%3Bflexible%20bands%26quot%3B%20are%20the%20hours%20that%20an%20employee%20can%20start%20or%20stop%20their%20workday.%20Under%20this%20schedule%2C%20workers%20can%20take%20breaks%20during%20the%20day%20without%20requesting%20them%20in%20advance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20a%20FWS%2C%20an%20agency%20may%20only%20have%20core%20hours%20from%2011%3A30%20a.m.%20to%201%3A30%20p.m.%20with%20flexible%20hours%20from%20nine%20to%20seven.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20an%20employee%20could%20work%20from%20nine-to-two%2C%20take%20a%20two-hour%20break%2C%20and%20then%20work%20until%20seven.%20Alternatively%2C%20the%20employee%20could%20start%20later%20and%20work%20until%20seven.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20no%20job%20is%20specifically%20excluded%20from%20working%20with%20this%20model%2C%20each%20government%20agency%20decides%20whether%20alternate%20work%20schedules%20are%20a%20good%20fit.%20Individual%20agencies%20also%20decide%20what%20parameters%20are%20in%20place%2C%20such%20as%20core%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20bunch%20of%20AWS%20possibilities%3B%20these%20are%20a%20few%20of%20the%20most%20common.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EAn%20extra%20day%20off%20every%20other%20week%3A%205%2F4-9%20or%209%2F80%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20schedule%2C%20employees%20work%2080%20hours%20over%20nine%20days%20instead%20of%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsually%2C%20it%20means%20working%20eight%209-hour%20days%2C%20one%208-hour%20day%2C%20and%20one%20day%20off%20every%20other%20week.%20So%20instead%20of%20working%20from%209-to-5%2C%20the%20employee%20may%20work%20until%206%20p.m.%20for%20eight%20out%20of%20the%20nine%20days.%20They%20would%20then%20work%20a%20normal%208-hour%20day%20on%20the%20ninth%20day%20and%20get%20the%2010th%20day%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EA%20three-day%20weekend%20every%20week%3A%204-10%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20type%20of%20CWS%2C%20employees%20work%20four%2010-hour%20days%20and%20get%20a%20three-day%20weekend%20at%20the%20end%20of%20every%20week.%20This%20might%20look%20like%20working%20from%208-to-6%20from%20Monday%20to%20Thursday%20every%20week.%20For%20some%20workers%2C%20this%20gives%20them%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgovernment-tech-contractor-job-overseas-travel-pay-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efreedom%20to%20travel%20every%20weekend%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EThe%20best%20of%20both%20worlds%3A%20maxiflex%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20maxiflex%2C%20employees%20combine%20flexible%20and%20compressed%20work%20schedules.%20This%20works%20if%20an%20agency%20has%20one%20or%20more%20days%20during%20the%20week%20without%20core%20hours.%20Employees%20here%20can%20take%20breaks%20during%20the%20day%20in%20addition%20to%20days%20off%20during%20the%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.opm.gov%2Fpolicy-data-oversight%2Fpay-leave%2Freference-materials%2Fhandbooks%2Falternative-work-schedules%2F%23Introduction%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOPM's%20website%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20a%20full%20glossary%20and%20breakdown%20of%20AWS%20terms%2C%20policies%2C%20and%20guidelines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falternative-government-work-weekend-schedule-explained-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708693201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65d77896a3bd891424f940e3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falternative-government-work-weekend-schedule-explained-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Alternative%20schedules%20allow%20workers%20to%20compress%20the%2080-hour%20pay%20period%20to%20get%20an%20extra%20day%20off%20or%20take%20daily%20breaks.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aaltchek%40insider.com%20(Ana%20Altchek)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falternative-government-work-weekend-schedule-explained-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Farmers%20Protest%20Should%20Turn%20the%20Spotlight%20on%20India's%20Impending%20Water%20Crisis%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27210340%2FEffect.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20farmers%20once%20again%20protest%20in%20India%20%E2%80%93%20three%20years%20on%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thethirdpole.net%2Fen%2Ffood%2Fclimate-crisis-is-foundation-of-indian-farmers-protests%2F%5C%22%3Ebiggest%20peaceful%20civil%20society%20protest%20in%20the%20world%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20it%20is%20worth%20remembering%20that%20agriculture%20was%20also%20a%20critical%20issue%20for%20the%20nation%20in%20its%20first%20decades.%20The%20country%E2%80%99s%20first%20prime%20minister%2C%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%2C%20bluntly%20stated%20that%20%E2%80%9Ceverything%20can%20wait%2C%20but%20not%20agriculture%E2%80%9D.%20This%20line%20of%20thinking%20eventually%20led%20to%20the%20Green%20Revolution%20of%20the%20late%201960s%2C%20forging%20India%E2%80%99s%20food%20security%20and%20providing%20much-needed%20revenue%20for%20some%20of%20its%20farmers.%20But%20back%20in%20the%20present%2C%20a%20looming%20water%20crisis%20has%20returned%20Indian%20agriculture%20to%20the%20spotlight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFarmers%E2%80%99%20grievances%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Green%20Revolution%20harnessed%20high-yield%20grain%20varieties%2C%20water-intensive%20practices%20(largely%20reliant%20on%20pumped%20groundwater)%20and%20heavy%20fertiliser%20use.%20Understanding%20that%20such%20investments%20would%20not%20be%20made%20by%20farmers%20without%20a%20guaranteed%20market%2C%20the%20Indian%20government%20also%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fwhat-is-the-basis-of-msp-6609668%2F%5C%22%3Ecreated%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0a%20minimum%20support%20price%20(MSP)%20for%20wheat%20in%201966-67.%20This%20set%20a%20base%20price%20for%20government%20procurement%20at%20a%20certain%20percentage%20above%20input%20costs%2C%20and%20therefore%20guaranteed%20farmers%20an%20assured%20buyer%3A%20even%20if%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20crop%20was%20not%20bought%20by%20the%20government%2C%20the%20MSP%20set%20a%20floor%20price%20for%20other%20buyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20the%20MSP%20regime%20covers%2023%20crops%3A%20varieties%20of%20cereals%2C%20pulses%20and%20some%20cash%20crops%20like%20sugarcane%20and%20cotton.%20It%20has%20been%20very%20successful%20in%20incentivising%20food%20production.%20So%2C%20instead%20of%20having%20to%20import%20grain%20as%20was%20the%20case%20before%20the%20Green%20Revolution%2C%20by%202017%20India%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feands.da.gov.in%2FPDF%2FAt%2520a%2520Glance%25202019%2520Eng.pdf%5C%22%3Ewas%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20first-largest%20global%20producer%20of%20pulses%20and%20jute%20and%20the%20second-largest%20global%20producer%20of%20wheat%2C%20rice%20and%20sugarcane.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20only%20the%20MSP%20for%20sugarcane%20is%20guaranteed%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F7053%2F1%2Fessential_commodities_act_1955.pdf%5C%22%3Eunder%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20Essential%20Commodities%20Act%20of%201955.%20At%20their%20heart%2C%20the%20most%20recent%20farmers%E2%80%99%20protests%20in%20India%20are%20a%20call%20for%20the%20MSP%20regime%20to%20be%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.downtoearth.org.in%2Fnews%2Fagriculture%2Ffarmers-reject-centre-s-new-msp-proposal-demand-guarantee-for-all-23-crops-94546%5C%22%3Elegalised%3C%2Fa%3E.%20To%20many%20Indian%20farmers%2C%20this%20is%20the%20only%20guarantee%20of%20some%20level%20of%20financial%20security.%20However%2C%20the%20gains%20of%20the%20Green%20Revolution%20and%20the%20MSP%20regime%20(in%20its%20current%20form)%20are%20currently%20being%20undone%20by%20a%20series%20of%20challenges%2C%20including%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFinite%20resources%20pushed%20to%20the%20brink%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%2019th-century%20India%2C%20the%20British%20viceroy%20Lord%20Curzon%20described%20the%20Indian%20economy%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%20gamble%20on%20the%20monsoons%E2%80%9D.%20When%20India%20began%20extracting%20its%20groundwater%20this%20issue%20faded%2C%20but%20new%20challenges%20were%20created.%20India%20is%20now%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funesdoc.unesco.org%2Fark%3A%2F48223%2Fpf0000380721%2FPDF%2F380721eng.pdf.multi%5C%22%3Ebiggest%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0user%20of%20groundwater%20in%20the%20world%20and%20water%20levels%20across%20India%20have%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcgwb.gov.in%2Fground-water-resource-assessment-0%5C%22%3Eplummeted%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0accordingly%3A%20in%202022%2C%20the%20condition%20of%2012%25%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20aquifers%20were%20categorised%20by%20the%20government%20as%20%E2%80%9Csemi-critical%E2%80%9D%3B%204%25%20as%20%E2%80%9Ccritical%E2%80%9D%3B%20and%2014%25%20as%20%E2%80%9Coverexploited%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02171714%2F6b5c8022-678b-4bd2-8840-7f28d05e4095.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02171714%2F6b5c8022-678b-4bd2-8840-7f28d05e4095.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02171714%2F6b5c8022-678b-4bd2-8840-7f28d05e4095-300x181.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02171714%2F6b5c8022-678b-4bd2-8840-7f28d05e4095-1024x619.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-683197%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22725%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20farmer%20in%20Trewa%20village%20of%20Jammu%20inspecting%20his%20rice%20crop%20which%20is%20ready%20for%20harvest.%20Ceasefire%20violation%20by%20Pakistan%20has%20raised%20clouds%20on%20the%20harvest%20season.%20Photo%3A%20By%20arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcgwb.gov.in%2Fground-water-resource-assessment-0%5C%22%3E87%25%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20extracted%20groundwater%20in%20India%20used%20for%20irrigation%2C%20the%20future%20looks%20bleak.%20A%202019%20Indian%20government%20report%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fbusiness-61965419%5C%22%3Eestimated%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.niti.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2019-08%2FCWMI-2.0-latest.pdf%5C%22%3E74%25%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20area%20where%20wheat%20is%20cultivated%2C%20and%2065%25%20of%20the%20area%20where%20rice%20is%20grown%2C%20will%20face%20water%20shortages.%20The%20most%20severely%20impacted%20parts%20of%20India%20are%20the%20semi-arid%20zones%20in%20its%20north-western%20region%2C%20where%20the%20planting%20of%20wheat%20and%20paddy%20(which%20form%20the%20bulk%20of%20government%20procurement)%20is%20the%20most%20intense.%20This%20is%20where%20most%20of%20the%20protesting%20farmers%20come%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20over-extraction%20of%20groundwater%20has%20also%20led%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mdpi.com%2F2073-4441%2F15%2F23%2F4125%5C%22%3Ehigher%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0concentrations%20of%20arsenic.%20This%20has%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleaseIframePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1809264%5C%22%3Etriggered%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0long-running%20health%20crises%20in%20states%20including%20Punjab%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Bihar%20and%20West%20Bengal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELastly%2C%20this%20focus%20on%20a%20limited%20range%20of%20crops%20means%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20indigenous%20seeds%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournalofethnicfoods.biomedcentral.com%2Farticles%2F10.1186%2Fs42779-019-0011-9%5C%22%3Edisappearing%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20that%20threatens%20a%20future%20for%20India%20in%20which%20it%20may%20be%20dependent%20on%20just%20a%20few%20types%20of%20seeds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20larger%20water%20crisis%20impacts%20agriculture%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20this%20is%20happening%20in%20the%20context%20of%20a%20challenging%20water%20future.%20India%E2%80%99s%20population%20number%20has%20taken%20off%20since%20independence%2C%20but%20its%20water%20resources%20remain%20the%20same.%20Water%20availability%20is%20estimated%20to%20be%20under%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1606099%5C%22%3E1%2C486%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0cubic%20metres%20per%20person%2C%20which%20is%20alarming%20given%20that%201%2C700%20cubic%20metres%20is%20usually%20considered%20the%20benchmark%20for%20water%20stress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20latest%20report%20on%20the%20Himalayan%20region%20by%20the%20International%20Centre%20for%20Integrated%20Mountain%20Development%20(ICIMOD)%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhkh.icimod.org%2Fhi-wise%2Fhi-wise-report%2F%5C%22%3Eestimates%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20region%20will%20hit%20%E2%80%9Cpeak%20water%E2%80%9D%20by%202050%2C%20after%20which%20water%20availability%20will%20decline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInadequate%20government%20response%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Green%20Revolution%20was%20conceptualised%20at%20a%20time%20when%20India%20had%20far%20less%20resources%20to%20understand%20its%20water%20needs%2C%20but%20half%20a%20century%20later%2C%20the%20government%20has%20nothing%20new%20to%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202020%2C%20it%20passed%20three%20farm%20laws%20that%20were%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Fbilltrack%2Fthe-farm-laws-repeal-bill-2021%5C%22%3Erepealed%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20November%202021.%20The%20laws%20pushed%20for%20greater%20market%20access%2C%20contract%20farming%2C%20and%20less%20regulation%20of%20essential%20commodities.%20They%20did%20not%20guarantee%20MSPs%20and%20in%20response%2C%20a%20number%20of%20state%20governments%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ftheprsblog%2Fcomparison-of-the-2020-central-farm-laws-with-the-amendments-proposed-by-states%5C%22%3Epassed%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0laws%20that%C2%A0%3Cem%3Edid%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Eguarantee%20MSPs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20weakening%20of%20the%20MSP%20regime%20was%20seen%20as%20an%20additional%20threat%20to%20the%20financial%20security%20of%20farmers%2C%20who%20are%20already%20dealing%20with%20lowered%20water%20tables%2C%20climate-induced%20floods%20and%20drought%20exacerbation%2C%20fluctuating%20monsoons%20and%20degraded%20soils%20from%20excessive%20fertiliser%20use%20%E2%80%93%20while%20these%20laws%20might%20have%20lowered%20procurement%20costs%20for%20the%20government%2C%20they%20did%20nothing%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20farming%20community%E2%80%99s%20myriad%20water%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20agricultural%20expert%20Devinder%20Sharma%20points%20out%2C%20farmers%20currently%20earn%20about%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fwatch-only-a-legally-binding-msp-can-really-help-farmers-weve-tried-all-permutations-and-combinations%5C%22%3EINR%2027%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0(USD%200.33)%20per%20day%20from%20farming%3A%20they%20need%20more%20support%2C%20not%20less.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20gained%20independence%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20Bengal%20famine%20in%201943%2C%20in%20which%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2019%2Fmar%2F29%2Fwinston-churchill-policies-contributed-to-1943-bengal-famine-study%5C%22%3Emillions%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0starved%20to%20death.%20Today%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1601902%5C%22%3Ehundreds%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20millions%20reliant%20on%20agriculture%20face%20a%20catastrophic%20future%20as%20water%20availability%20dwindles.%20The%20government%20should%20know%20by%20now%20that%20everything%20can%20wait%2C%20but%20not%20agriculture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thethirdpole.net%2Fen%2Ffood%2Fanalysis-as-farmers-protest-india-must-urgently-deal-with-its-water-crisis%2F%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20first%20appeared%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thethirdpole.net%2Fen%2F%5C%22%3EThird%20Pole%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOmair%20Ahmad%20is%20the%20managing%20editor%20for%20South%20Asia%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Third%20Pole%3Cem%3E.%20He%20has%20worked%20as%20a%20political%20analyst%20and%20journalist%2C%20with%20a%20particular%20focus%20on%20the%20Himalayan%20region.%20He%20is%20the%20author%20of%20a%20political%20history%20of%20Bhutan%2C%20and%20a%20few%20novels.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708693145000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27210340%2FEffect.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Ffarmers-protest-should-turn-the-spotlight-on-indias-impending-water-crisis%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22With%C2%A087%25%C2%A0of%20extracted%20groundwater%20in%20India%20used%20for%20irrigation%2C%20the%20future%20looks%20bleak.%20A%202019%20Indian%20government%20report%C2%A0estimated%C2%A0that%C2%A074%25%C2%A0of%20the%20area%20where%20wheat%20is%20cultivated%2C%20and%2065%25%20of%20the%20area%20where%20rice%20is%20grown%2C%20will%20face%20water%20shortages.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Ffarmers-protest-should-turn-the-spotlight-on-indias-impending-water-crisis%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22An%20Alaska%20Airlines%20passenger%20stabbed%20an%20off-duty%20law%20enforcement%20officer%20with%20an%20improvised%20weapon%20made%20from%20pens%2C%20affidavit%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224606%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20Alaska%20Airlines%20plane%20takeoff%20from%20San%20Francisco%20International%20Airport%20(SFO)%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20California%2C%20United%20States%20on%20February%2021%2C%202024%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65d885c26080194819f9a229%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223070%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20Alaska%20Airlines%20plane.%3Cp%3ETayfun%20Coskun%2FAnadolu%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20man%20stabbed%20a%20fellow%20passenger%20with%20several%20pens%20bundled%20together%2C%20an%20affidavit%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20adds%20that%20Julio%20Alvarez%20Lopez%20told%20FBI%20agents%20he%20believed%20he%20was%20being%20followed%20by%20the%20mafia.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20was%20indicted%20on%20one%20count%20of%20assault%20with%20a%20dangerous%20weapon.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falaska-airlines-ceo-mad-and-angry-with-boeing-after-blowout-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAlaska%20Airlines%3C%2Fa%3E%20passenger%20stabbed%20an%20off-duty%20law%20enforcement%20officer%20with%20an%20improvised%20weapon%2C%20an%20FBI%20agent's%20affidavit%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJulio%20Alvarez%20Lopez%20was%20indicted%20on%20one%20count%20of%20assault%20with%20a%20dangerous%20weapon%20by%20a%20grand%20jury%20in%20Nevada%20District%20Court%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20affidavit%20says%20Lopez%20admitted%20he%20made%20the%20weapon%20before%20the%20flight%2C%20by%20bundling%20pens%20together%20with%20a%20rubber%20band.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20and%20the%20victim%2C%20referred%20to%20as%20CR%2C%20were%20flying%20from%20Seattle%20to%20Las%20Vegas%20on%20January%2024.%20CR%20was%20sat%20across%20the%20aisle%20from%20Lopez%2C%20per%20the%20court%20document.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECR%20is%20listed%20in%20court%20documents%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bsworn%20law%20enforcement%20officer%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20it%20is%20not%20clear%20for%20which%20agency%20he%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20witness%20who%20sat%20next%20to%20Lopez%20said%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bfidgety%26quot%3B%20during%20the%20flight%2C%20putting%20his%20gloves%20on%20and%20off%2C%20and%20avoiding%20eye%20contact%2C%20per%20the%20affidavit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20adds%20that%20as%20the%20plane%20began%20its%20initial%20descent%2C%20Lopez%20went%20to%20the%20bathroom%20%26quot%3Bfor%20a%20while%26quot%3B%20and%20then%20came%20out%20and%20started%20attacking%20CR.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20victim's%20wife%20was%20screaming%20and%20%26quot%3Bthere%20was%20blood%20everywhere%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20witness%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Lopez%20began%20moving%20toward%20the%20front%20of%20the%20plane%2C%20CR%20ordered%20him%20to%20sit%20down%20before%20the%20flight%20crew%20restrained%20him%20with%20flex%20cuffs%2C%20they%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20being%20taken%20into%20custody%2C%20the%20affidavit%20says%20Lopez%20said%20that%20he%20thought%20the%20mafia%20was%20chasing%20him%2C%20and%20he%20was%20seeking%20asylum%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20FBI%20agents%2C%20Lopez%20said%20he%20believed%20CR%20was%20part%20of%20a%20cartel%20and%20was%20following%20him%2C%20the%20affidavit%20says.%20The%20affidavit%20does%20not%20specify%20which%20cartel%20Lopez%20was%20referring%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20adds%20that%20Lopez%20said%20he%20was%20trying%20to%20stab%20CR%20in%20the%20eye%20to%20reach%20his%20brain%20and%20kill%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlaska%20Airlines%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider%2C%20sent%20outside%20US%20working%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20motion%20filed%20Thursday%2C%20Lopez%20said%20he%20no%20longer%20wants%20his%20court-appointed%20attorney%20to%20represent%20him.%20A%20federal%20public%20defender%20requested%20a%20conference%20to%20discuss%20Lopez's%20representation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fman-stabbed-alaska-airlines-passenger-with-makeshift-weapon-affidavit-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708693009000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65d8874890413ab8e1d64db1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fman-stabbed-alaska-airlines-passenger-with-makeshift-weapon-affidavit-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Julio%20Alvarez%20Lopez%20told%20FBI%20agents%20he%20stabbed%20the%20man%20in%20the%20eye%20with%20pens%20because%20he%20believed%20he%20was%20following%20him%2C%20an%20affidavit%20says.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22psyme%40insider.com%20(Pete%20Syme)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fman-stabbed-alaska-airlines-passenger-with-makeshift-weapon-affidavit-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%