l%20in%20October.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708684260000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-02%2Fmv5p6c0c_shamima-begum-reuters_625x300_21_February_19.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fshamima-begum-woman-who-joined-isis-in-syria-loses-appeal-against-removal-of-uk-citizenship-5112713%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20British-born%20woman%20who%20went%20to%20Syria%20as%20a%20schoolgirl%20to%20join%20Islamic%20State%20on%20Friday%20lost%20her%20latest%20appeal%20over%20the%20removal%20of%20her%20British%20citizenship.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fshamima-begum-woman-who-joined-isis-in-syria-loses-appeal-against-removal-of-uk-citizenship-5112713%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fshamima-begum-woman-who-joined-isis-in-syria-loses-appeal-against-removal-of-uk-citizenship-5112713%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fshamima-begum-woman-who-joined-isis-in-syria-loses-appeal-against-removal-of-uk-citizenship-5112713%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Tale%20of%20Two%20Global%20Trade%20Ministerial%20Summits%20in%20West%20Asia%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F22174245%2FEffect-2024-02-22T174216.655.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20objectives%20of%20two%20global%20trade%20ministerial%20summits%20in%20West%20Asia%2C%20convened%20amid%20the%20backdrop%20of%20war%2C%20a%20deteriorating%20international%20order%2C%20and%20mounting%20geopolitical%20and%20geoeconomic%20tensions%2C%20appear%20to%20be%20at%20odds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20summits%20has%20concluded%2C%20while%20the%20other%20is%20scheduled%20to%20commence%20on%20February%2026.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202001%2C%20the%20fourth%20ministerial%20conference%20of%20the%20World%20Trade%20Organization%20was%20held%20in%20Doha.%20It%20took%20place%20after%20violent%20anti-globalisation%20riots%20in%20Seattle%20at%20the%20WTO%E2%80%99s%20third%20ministerial%20conference%20in%20December%201999.%20Then%20there%20was%20a%20pause%20for%20almost%20two%20years.%20The%20Doha%20meeting%20coincided%20with%20the%20war%20on%20terror%20following%20the%209%2F11%20attacks.%20The%20US%20touted%20trade%20as%20a%20panacea%20for%20global%20peace%2C%20launching%20a%20new%20round%20of%20trade%20negotiations%20with%20the%20European%20Union%20and%20other%20industrialised%20countries%2C%20famously%20known%20as%20the%20Doha%20Round%20in%20the%20Qatari%20capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Doha%20Round%20ambitiously%20covered%20various%20issues%20ranging%20from%20agriculture%20to%20development%2C%20and%20improving%20the%20elements%20introduced%20in%20the%20Uruguay%20Round%20commitments%20as%20set%20out%20in%20the%20WTO%20agreements.%20It%20also%20discussed%20Singapore%20issues%20including%20trade%20and%20investment%2C%20competition%20policy%2C%20trade%20facilitation%2C%20and%20government%20procurement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20and%20the%20European%20Union%20played%20pivotal%20roles%20in%20initiating%20the%20ambitious%20Doha%20work%20programme.%20However%2C%20India%20and%20numerous%20developing%20nations%20resisted%20launching%20a%20new%20round%20of%20trade%20negotiations%20due%20to%20systemic%20concerns.%20Their%20rationale%20stemmed%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20many%20countries%20had%20yet%20to%20fully%20absorb%20and%20implement%20the%20commitments%20from%20the%20preceding%20Uruguay%20Round%2C%20which%20laid%20the%20foundation%20for%20the%20establishment%20of%20the%20WTO.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20there%20was%20little%20room%20for%20a%20new%20ambitious%20round%20of%20negotiations.%20But%20India%20was%20isolated%20at%20Doha%20when%20some%20other%20developing%20countries%20fell%20prey%20to%20the%20pressure%20tactics%20and%20arm-twisting%20adopted%20by%20the%20US%20and%20the%20EU.%20Subsequently%2C%20the%20two%20trans-Atlantic%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fepw.in%2Fjournal%2F2014%2F25%2Fweb-exclusives%2Fdoha-round.html%5C%22%3Eelephants%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20their%20allies%20thwarted%20the%20Doha%20round%20after%20pocketing%20what%20they%20wanted%2C%20namely%2C%20the%20trade%20facilitation%20agreement.%20The%20developing%20countries%20who%20pinned%20their%20hopes%20on%20several%20developmental%20outcomes%20in%20various%20areas%20of%20the%20Doha%20work%20programme%20were%20left%20high%20and%20dry.%20The%20moral%20of%20the%20story%20is%20that%20a%20multilateral%20round%20of%20trade%20negotiations%20based%20on%20what%20is%20called%20Single%20Undertaking%2C%20implying%20nothing%20is%20agreed%20upon%20until%20everything%20is%20agreed%2C%20has%20been%20decimated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFast%20forward%20to%20Abu%20Dhabi%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwenty-three%20years%20after%20dismantling%20the%20Doha%20round%2C%20trade%20ministers%20of%20164%20countries%20will%20convene%20in%20Abu%20Dhabi%20for%20the%20WTO%E2%80%99s%2013th%20ministerial%20conference%20on%20February%2026.%20In%20a%20letter%20sent%20to%20the%20trade%20ministers%20on%20February%2016%2C%20WTO%20Director-General%20Ngozi%20Okonjo-Iweala%20admitted%20that%20%E2%80%9Ca%20number%20of%20outstanding%20issues%20remain%20to%20be%20resolved%20at%20the%20ministerial%20level%20as%20reflected%20in%20the%20brackets%20in%20the%20texts.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20multilateral%20parlance%2C%20the%20bracketed%20text%20implies%20that%20there%20is%20no%20agreement%20or%20convergence%20yet%20on%20the%20proposed%20language.%20She%20urged%20ministers%20%E2%80%9Cto%20focus%20on%20issues%20that%20are%20bracketed%20and%20not%20reopen%20areas%20where%20there%20is%20convergence.%E2%80%9D%20But%20she%20seems%20to%20have%20ignored%20the%20normal%20rule%20that%20in%20multilateral%20trade%20negotiations%2C%20member%20countries%20retain%20the%20sovereign%20prerogative%20to%20open%20or%20refrain%20from%20opening%20discussions%20on%20specific%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20draft%20package%20comprises%20texts%20including%20the%20draft%20%E2%80%9CAbu%20Dhabi%20Ministerial%20Declaration%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20draft%20text%20on%20%E2%80%9CAgriculture%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20very%20short%20draft%20text%20on%20%E2%80%9CDispute%20Settlement%20Reform%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20draft%20text%20on%20%E2%80%9Cfisheries%20subsidies%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20%C2%A0%E2%80%9CWork%20Program%20on%20Electronic%20Commerce%E2%80%9D.%20Additionally%2C%20it%20includes%20discussions%20on%20%E2%80%9CMinisterial%20Conversations%20on%20Trade%20and%20Sustainable%20Development%2C%20including%20Trade%20and%20Industrial%20Policy%20and%20Policy%20Space%20for%20Development%2C%20and%20on%20Trade%20and%20Inclusion%2C%20among%20other%20information.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20issues%20such%20as%20Industrial%20Policy%20and%20Policy%20Space%20raised%20by%20developing%20countries%20and%20previously%20dismissed%20as%20breaches%20of%20WTO%20commitments%2C%20have%20found%20their%20way%20onto%20the%20Abu%20Dhabi%20Ministerial%20Agenda.%20This%20shift%2C%20attributed%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F5b2a82e0-fb81-4a41-b3e5-5cb0ab899b4d%5C%22%3EBiden%3C%2Fa%3E%20administration%E2%80%99s%20embrace%20of%20industrial%20policies%20and%20sustainable%20development%2C%20perhaps%20indicates%20the%20evolving%20influence%20of%20Uncle%20Sam%20on%20the%20WTO.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20resolving%20mandated%20issues%20like%20the%20permanent%20solution%20for%20public%20stockholding%20programmes%20for%20food%20security%2C%20which%20has%20been%20pending%20since%202015%2C%20the%20termination%20of%20the%20e-commerce%20moratorium%20for%20not%20levying%20customs%20duties%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.wto.org%2Fdol2fe%2FPages%2FSS%2Fdirectdoc.aspx%3Ffilename%3Dq%3A%2FWT%2FMIN22%2F32.pdf%26Open%3DTrue%5C%22%3Eagreed%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%2012th%20ministerial%20conference%20in%20Geneva%20in%20June%202022%2C%20and%20restoring%20a%20two-tier%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.wto.org%2Fdol2fe%2FPages%2FSS%2Fdirectdoc.aspx%3Ffilename%3Dq%3A%2FWT%2FMIN22%2F24.pdf%26Open%3DTrue%5C%22%3Edispute%3C%2Fa%3E%20settlement%20system%2C%20something%20else%20is%20underway.%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20ministerial%20mandates%2C%20which%20are%20considered%20sacrosanct%2C%20are%20set%20aside%20and%20goalposts%20are%20shifted%20by%20the%20dominant%20members%2C%20particularly%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%20is%20a%20leader%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20look%20at%20India%20as%20a%20leader%2C%20and%20we%20thank%20that%20as%20a%20leader%2C%20India%20has%20a%20lot%20to%20do%20in%20terms%20of%20making%20sure%20we%20have%20a%20successful%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Feconomy%2Fforeign-trade%2Fas-a-leader-india-must-ensure-a-successful-meet-wto-dg-ngozi-okonjo-iweala%2Farticleshow%2F107831961.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3EMC%3C%2Fa%3E%2013%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20DG%20said%2C%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20an%20Indian%20news%20daily.%C2%A0She%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Feconomy%2Fforeign-trade%2Fas-a-leader-india-must-ensure-a-successful-meet-wto-dg-ngozi-okonjo-iweala%2Farticleshow%2F107831961.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ehopes%3C%2Fa%3E%20India%2C%20Brazil%2C%20and%20South%20Africa%20%E2%80%9Cwill%20work%20together%20to%20ensure%20MC%2013%20is%20a%20success%E2%80%A6%20the%20entire%20package%E2%80%A6%20not%20one%20issue%20or%20the%20other%2C%20it%20is%20across%20the%20board.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20her%20elevating%20comments%20on%20India%20to%20take%20the%20leadership%20role%20seem%20somewhat%20odd%2C%20when%20one%20considers%20developments%20in%20the%20small%20group%20meetings%20behind%20the%20scenes.%20The%20WTO%20establishment%20appears%20to%20be%20working%20furiously%20behind%20the%20scenes%20at%20isolating%20India%20on%20three%20mandated%20issues%20%E2%80%93%20the%20permanent%20solution%20for%20public%20stockholding%20programmes%20for%20food%20security%2C%20the%20moratorium%20on%20customs%20duties%20on%20electronic%20transmissions%2C%20and%20investment%20facilitation%20for%20development%2C%20said%20people%20familiar%20with%20the%20ongoing%20discussions%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20the%20DG%E2%80%99s%20remarks%20against%20the%20stand%20adopted%20by%20India%20and%20South%20Africa%20at%20a%20special%20general%20council%20meeting%20on%20February%2014%20were%20rarely%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwn.my%2Ftitle2%2Fwto.info%2F2024%2Fti240212.htm%5C%22%3Ewitnessed%3C%2Fa%3E.%20India%20and%20South%20Africa%20raised%20procedural%20as%20well%20as%20systemic%20issues%20against%20a%20proposed%20plurilateral%20agreement%2C%20called%20the%20Investment%20Facilitation%20for%20Development%20(IFD)%2C%20on%20grounds%20that%20it%20went%20against%20the%20WTO%E2%80%99s%20core%20principles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20WTO%20rules%2C%20as%20set%20out%20in%20Articles%20IX%20and%20X%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wto.org%2Fenglish%2Fdocs_e%2Flegal_e%2F04-wto_e.htm%5C%22%3EMarrakesh%3C%2Fa%3E%20Agreement%2C%20which%20led%20to%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20WTO%2C%20members%20have%20to%20arrive%20at%20any%20decision%20based%20on%20prior%20consensus%20to%20negotiate%20a%20plurilateral%20agreement.%20India%20and%20South%20Africa%20have%20consistently%20opposed%20the%20proposed%20plurilateral%20(among%20a%20group%20of%20countries)%20agreement%20on%20IFD%20for%20violating%20rules%20and%20also%20on%20systemic%20grounds.%20It%20may%20well%20be%20the%20case%20that%20the%20IFD%2C%20which%20has%20been%20spearheaded%20by%20China%20since%202016%2C%20despite%20a%20lack%20of%20consensus%2C%20is%20currently%20supported%20by%20more%20than%20two-thirds%20of%20the%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20rules-based%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wto.org%2Fenglish%2Fdocs_e%2Flegal_e%2F04-wto_e.htm%5C%22%3Econsensus-driven%3C%2Fa%3E%20(as%20per%20Article%20IX%20of%20the%20Marrakesh%20Agreement)%20intergovernmental%2C%20multilateral%20trade%20organisation%2C%20new%20initiatives%20or%20agreements%2C%20whether%20multilateral%20or%20plurilateral%2C%20cannot%20simply%20be%20imposed%20based%20on%20a%20brute%20majority.%20This%20is%20especially%20true%20when%20such%20initiatives%20have%20consistently%20faced%20rejection%20since%20the%20WTO%E2%80%99s%20fifth%20ministerial%20meeting%20in%20Cancun%2C%20Mexico%2C%20in%202003.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20sake%20of%20success%20in%20Abu%20Dhabi%2C%20it%20would%20be%20imprudent%20to%20break%20the%20rules%20and%20create%20a%20wave%20of%20impunity.%20It%20is%20essential%20that%20even%20if%20an%20agreement%20is%20advanced%20by%20more%20than%20120%20countries%2C%20multilateral%20rules%20as%20enshrined%20in%20the%20Marrakesh%20Agreement%20ought%20to%20take%20precedence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncreasingly%2C%20the%20MC%2013%20appears%20to%20be%20an%20exercise%20in%20weakening%20the%20core%20principles%20of%20the%20multilateral%20trading%20system%20to%20advance%20controversial%20new%20issues%20by%20adopting%20seemingly%20dubious%20forms%20of%20decision-making%2C%20such%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98responsible%20consensus%2C%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98flexible%20consensus%2C%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98constructive%20consensus%2C%E2%80%99%20to%20jettison%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wto.org%2Fenglish%2Fdocs_e%2Flegal_e%2F04-wto_e.htm%5C%22%3EArticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20IX%20of%20the%20Marrakesh%20Agreement.%20So%2C%20a%20new%20road%20to%20cherry-picking%20issues%20appears%20to%20be%20underway%20depending%20on%20the%20power%20and%20status%20of%20the%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20process%2C%20what%20is%20being%20done%20to%20multilateralism%20seems%20somewhat%20akin%20to%20what%20had%20happened%20to%20Africa%20more%20than%20a%20century%20ago%2C%20i.e.%2C%20the%20Scramble%2F%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Ftopic%2FWestern-colonialism%2FPartition-of-Africa%5C%22%3EPartition%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Africa.%20Well%2C%20India%20and%20South%20Africa%20appear%20to%20be%20coming%20in%20the%20way%20of%20the%20partition%20of%20the%20multilateral%20trading%20system%20that%20may%20take%20place%20at%20Abu%20Dhabi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrade%20and%20environment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20controversial%20issue%20that%20is%20being%20pushed%20by%20the%20US%20and%20the%20EU%20is%20on%20trade%20and%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20DG%20even%20proposed%20language%20on%20this%20issue%20which%20remains%20in%20the%20square%20brackets%3A%20%E2%80%9C%5BWe%20reaffirm%20the%20importance%20of%20the%20contribution%20that%20the%20multilateral%20trading%20system%20can%20make%20to%20addressing%20global%20environmental%20challenges%2C%20including%20climate%20change%20and%20related%20natural%20disasters%2C%20loss%20of%20biodiversity%20and%20pollution%2C%20and%20promoting%20the%20UN%202030%20Agenda%20and%20its%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%20(SDGs)%20in%20its%20economic%2C%20social%20and%20environmental%20dimensions%2C%20insofar%20as%20they%20relate%20to%20WTO%20mandates%20and%20in%20a%20manner%20consistent%20with%20the%20Members%E2%80%99%20respective%20needs%20and%20concerns%20at%20different%20levels%20of%20economic%20development.%20We%20recognise%20the%20ongoing%20efforts%20of%20the%20Committee%20on%20Trade%20and%20Environment%20(CTE)%2C%20including%20hosting%20Thematic%20Sessions%20to%20allow%20Members%20to%20deepen%20discussions%2C%20including%20on%20the%20relationship%20between%20trade%20measures%20and%20environmental%20measures.%20The%20CTE%20will%20provide%20a%20factual%20report%20on%20its%20activities%20to%20the%20General%20Council%20before%20the%2014th%20Session%20of%20the%20Ministerial%20Conference%2C%20including%20possible%20recommendations.%5D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20time%20when%20unilateral%20trade%20measures%20such%20as%20the%20EU%E2%80%99s%20controversial%20unilateral%20carbon%20border%20adjustment%20mechanism%20(CBAM)%20or%20carbon%20border%20tax%20are%20poised%20to%20enter%20an%2018-month%20trial%20period%20starting%20October%201%2C%20it%20appears%20that%20the%20WTO%20is%20offering%20its%20support.%20The%20proposed%20penalties%20under%20CBAM%20range%20from%20%E2%82%AC50%20per%20tonne%20of%20carbon%20emissions%2C%20with%20formal%20introduction%20slated%20for%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20signed%20piece%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20on%20September%2028%2C%20the%20EU%20Commissioner%20for%20Economy%2C%20Paolo%20Gentiloni%2C%20extolled%20the%20virtues%20of%20the%20proposed%20CBAM%2C%20claiming%20that%20it%20is%20%E2%80%9Cfully%20compatible%20with%20the%20WTO%20rules%E2%80%9D%20and%20it%20is%20not%20about%20trade%20protection.%20However%2C%20these%20claims%20are%20being%20challenged%20by%20several%20members%2C%20who%20argue%20that%20the%20CBAM%20allegedly%20violates%20the%20core%20WTO%20rules%20and%20worse%20still%2C%20it%20goes%20against%20the%20Paris%20Climate%20Change%20Agreement%20of%202015%2C%20particularly%20the%20principle%20of%20common%20but%20differentiated%20responsibilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20EU%20and%20the%20US%20seem%20to%20be%20in%20no%20mood%20to%20abide%20by%20the%20multilateral%20rules%20as%20set%20out%20in%20the%20Paris%20Climate%20Change%20Agreement.%20Instead%2C%20they%20are%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20deploying%20unilateral%2C%20trade-related%20measures%20to%20address%20climate%20change%20in%20the%20developed%20world%2C%20which%20risks%20damaging%20the%20development%20prospects%20in%20developing%20countries%2C%20including%20the%20BRICS%20(Brazil%2C%20Russia%2C%20India%2C%20China%2C%20and%20South%20Africa).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20UNCATD%20report%20last%20year%2C%20the%20EU%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9CCarbon%20Border%20Adjustment%20Mechanism%20(CBAM)%2C%20which%20would%20impose%20a%20carbon%20tariff%20on%20imports%20into%20the%20EU%20from%20non-EU%20countries%2C%20(is)%20based%20on%20the%20level%20of%20carbon%20emissions%20generated%20in%20the%20production%20of%20the%20imported%20products.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CBAM%E2%80%99s%20effect%20on%20reducing%20greenhouse%20gas%20(GHG)%20emissions%20is%20projected%20to%20be%20minimal%2C%20accounting%20for%20less%20than%200.1%25%20decrease.%20However%2C%20its%20impact%20on%20energy-intensive%20exports%20from%20BRICS%20countries%20to%20the%20EU%20is%20expected%20to%20result%20in%20a%20decline%20ranging%20from%2015%25%20to%2026%25%2C%20contingent%20on%20the%20carbon%20pricing%20scenarios%20implemented.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20real%20income%20of%20BRICS%20may%20fall%20between%20%244%20billion%20to%20%247%20billion%20with%20maximum%20fall%20in%20the%20Russian%20Federation%20(%242.5%20billion)%2C%20followed%20by%20India%20(%241.6%20billion)%20and%20South%20Africa%20(%241.3%20billion)%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20suggested%2C%20adding%20that%2C%20%E2%80%9CSuch%20measures%20which%20reduce%20real%20incomes%20in%20BRICS%20will%20make%20it%20more%20challenging%20for%20these%20countries%20to%20progress%20on%20their%20climate%20goals.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20growing%20adaptation%20costs%20to%20address%20accelerating%20climate%20change%2C%20developing%20countries%20will%20be%20hit%20hard.%20%E2%80%9CUndoubtedly%2C%20economic%20diversification%2C%20technological%20progress%2C%20robust%20government%20finances%2C%20and%20reliable%20sources%20of%20foreign%20exchange%20are%20the%20preconditions%20for%20successful%20climate%20change%20adaptation%20and%20mitigation%20strategies%20in%20the%20developing%20world%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20suggested.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20short%2C%20the%20Abu%20Dhabi%20meeting%20is%20a%20litmus%20test%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20resolve%20to%20stand%20up%20for%20its%20stated%20positions%20or%20make%20compromises%20without%20securing%20credible%20results%2C%20as%20had%20happened%20in%20the%20previous%20ministerial%20meetings.%20It%20has%20become%20a%20familiar%20tactic%20to%20project%20India%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cleader%E2%80%9D%20only%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20Modi%20government%20does%20not%20pursue%20its%20issues%20in%20the%20multilateral%20fora%20when%20push%20comes%20to%20shove.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708684219000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F22174245%2FEffect-2024-02-22T174216.655.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftrade%2Fthe-tale-of-two-global-trade-ministerial-summits-in-west-asia%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22With%20one%20summit%20concluded%20and%20another%20set%20to%20begin%20on%20February%2026%2C%20tensions%20rise%20as%20trade%20ministers%20gather%20amidst%20war%2C%20a%20deteriorating%20international%20landscape%2C%20and%20escalating%20geopolitical%20and%20geoeconomic%20pressures.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftrade%2Fthe-tale-of-two-global-trade-ministerial-summits-in-west-asia%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rani%20Mukerji%20stuns%20in%20shimmery%20black%20saree%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708684200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107921893%2Cimgsize-39792.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fweb-stories%2Frani-mukerji-is-a-vision-to-behold-in-a-shimmery-black-saree%2Fphotostory%2F107921893.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F107921893.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5