n%E2%80%99s%20voices%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20labour%2C%20normalisation%20of%20violence%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scirp.org%2Fjournal%2Fpaperinformation%3Fpaperid%3D104116%5C%22%3Epower%20dynamics%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0between%20health%20professionals%20and%20patients%2C%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.emerald.com%2Finsight%2Fcontent%2Fdoi%2F10.1108%2F978-1-80382-255-620231014%2Ffull%2Fhtml%5C%22%3Etraining%20models%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20ignore%20obstetric%20violence%20practices%20all%20exacerbate%20the%20situation%20in%20labour%20rooms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.academia.edu%2F59035191%2F_Hospitals_have_some_procedures_that_seem_dehumanising_to_me_Experiences_of_abortion_related_obstetric_violence_in_Brazil_Chile_and_Ecuador%5C%22%3EAbortion-related%20obstetric%20violence%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0has%20been%20more%20frequent%20in%20settings%20that%20legally%20restrict%20abortions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThreats%20and%20violence%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20midwifes%20during%20birthing%20has%20been%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F34872035%2F%5C%22%3Ecompared%20to%20rape%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20obstetric%20violence%20is%20also%20sometimes%20termed%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scirp.org%2Freference%2Freferencespapers%3Freferenceid%3D2861807%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cbirth%20rape%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9C.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQualitative%20studies%20show%20that%20such%20abusive%20experiences%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F37018999%2F%5C%22%3Eexacerbate%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3Evictims%E2%80%99%20anxiety%2C%20helplessness%2C%20anger%20and%20fear%2C%20with%20many%20lapsing%20into%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F36862241%2F%5C%22%3Epostpartum%20depression%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0or%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F23581206%2F%5C%22%3Epost-traumatic%20stress%20disorders%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20is%20no%20specific%20law%20against%20obstetric%20violence%20under%20Indian%20law%2C%20it%20is%20considered%20a%20human%20rights%20violation%20under%20international%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20January%202023%2C%20the%20Inter-American%20Court%20of%20Human%20Rights%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2023%2F03%2F06%2Fobstetric-violence-violates-human-rights%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%2520January%25202023%252C%2520the%2520court%2Cchildbirth%2520and%2520post%252Dpartum.%25E2%2580%259D%5C%22%3E%C2%A0recognised%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0obstetric%20violence%20as%20a%20human%20rights%20violation%20after%20a%20pregnant%20woman%20in%20Argentina%2C%20who%20was%20found%20to%20have%20a%20dead%20foetus%20in%20her%20ninth%20month%20of%20pregnancy%2C%20died%20of%20cardiac%20arrest%20after%20she%20was%20hospitalised%20to%20induce%20labour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.corteidh.or.cr%2Fdocs%2Fcomunicados%2Fcp_02_2023_eng.pdf%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0she%20had%20not%20received%20appropriate%20medical%20treatment%20considering%20known%20risk%20factors%20of%20her%20pregnancy%20which%20led%20to%20death%20of%20the%20foetus%2C%20and%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20given%20necessary%20information%20on%20treatment%20alternatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20the%20UN%20Committee%20on%20the%20Elimination%20of%20All%20Forms%20of%20Discrimination%20Against%20Women%20found%20that%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fohrh.law.ox.ac.uk%2Fobstetric-violence-as-a-violation-of-human-rights-cedaws-second-decision-a-welcome-addition-but-not-enough%2F%5C%22%3E%C2%A0forced%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0C-section%20delivery%20without%20informed%20consent%20was%20performed%20on%20a%20Spanish%20woman%20%E2%80%94%20who%20was%20also%20forbidden%20from%20eating%20during%20labour%20%E2%80%94%20had%20been%20subjected%20to%20obstetric%20violence%20and%20violation%20of%20her%20human%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20countries%20do%20recognise%20obstetric%20violence%20in%20national%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EObstetric%20violence%20as%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F20926074%2F%5C%22%3Elegal%20term%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0was%20introduced%20in%20Venezuela%20in%202007%20when%20the%20%E2%80%9COrganic%20Law%20on%20the%20Right%20of%20Women%20to%20a%20Life%20Free%20of%20Violence%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.law.cornell.edu%2Fwomen-and-justice%2Fresource%2Fley_org%25C3%25A1nica_sobre_derecho_de_las_mujeres_a_una_vida_libre_de_violencia_cap%25C3%25ADtulo_(organic_law_on%5C%22%3Ecame%20into%20force%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Several%20other%20countries%20in%20South%20and%20Central%20America%20have%20recognised%20obstetric%20violence%20as%20a%20legal%20concept%2C%20including%20Argentina%2C%20Mexico%2C%20and%20Uruguay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20concerns%20about%20different%20types%20of%20obstetric%20violence%20raised%20by%20human%20rights%20organisations%2C%20social%20movements%20and%20academics%2C%20there%20is%20a%20dearth%20of%20investigations%2C%20evidence-based%20record%20creation%20and%20legislation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClear%20statistical%20data%20on%20the%20prevalence%20of%20obstetric%20violence%20worldwide%20is%20missing%2C%20despite%20campaigns%20and%20living%20in%20an%20age%20marked%20by%20digitisation%2C%20artificial%20intelligence%20and%20ethical%20governance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGovernments%20have%20largely%20ignored%20the%20issue%2C%20and%20this%20medical%20malpractice%20has%20been%20overlooked%20and%20loosely%20defined%20by%20public%20and%20private%20healthcare%20institutions.%20This%20can%20be%20pinned%20to%20the%20failure%20of%20the%20medical%20establishment%20to%20confront%20maternal%20health%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHealthcare%20institutions%20and%20professionals%20could%20be%20first%20to%20be%20held%20responsible%20for%20episodes%20of%20obstetric%20violence%20on%20their%20premises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECarefully%20chartered%20management%20and%20policy%20strategies%20to%20identify%20obstetric%20violence%20%E2%80%94%20and%20track%20how%20it%20applies%20along%20lines%20of%20class%2C%20gender%2C%20race%2C%20and%20medical%20power%20%E2%80%94%20would%20help%20offer%20respite%20to%20expecting%20mothers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20these%20practices%20are%20not%20treated%2C%20progress%20bywomen%E2%80%99s%20reproductive%20rights%20movements%2C%20which%20have%20fought%20hard%20for%20dignity%20of%20care%20and%20bodily%20integrity%2C%20could%20backslide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHealthcare%20institutions%20and%20professionals%20could%20be%20made%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.samj.org.za%2Findex.php%2Fsamj%2Farticle%2Fview%2F10708%5C%22%3Efully%20accountable%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20unethical%20practices%20inside%20or%20outside%20the%20labour%20room%20which%20diminish%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20dignity%20during%20delivery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judicial%20system%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20recognising%20and%20punishing%20obstetric%20violence%20in%20India%20needs%20strengthening.%20The%20law%20could%20introduce%20safeguards%20for%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights%20and%20choices%20in%20obstetric%20care%20%E2%80%94%20ensuring%20each%20mother%20can%20choose%20her%20birthing%20position%2C%20support%20person%20and%20pain%20control%20(including%20non-pharmacological%20methods)%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20she%20is%20given%20equitable%20treatment%20irrespective%20of%20caste%20and%20socio-economic%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EObstetric%20violence%20legislation%20in%20India%20could%20clearly%20lay%20down%20the%20authority%2C%20definitions%20and%20remedies%20for%20physical%20abuse%2C%20verbal%20abuse%2C%20non-confidential%20and%20non-consented%20care%2C%20negligent%20and%20discriminatory%20care%2C%20and%20non-dignified%20care%20towards%20women%20in%20all%20stages%20of%20pregnancy%2C%20childbirth%20and%20new%20motherhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20laws%20could%20cover%20private%20and%20public%20births%2C%20as%20well%20as%20home%20births.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdoption%20and%20use%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F33082123%2F%5C%22%3Ebirth%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20public%20and%20private%20healthcare%20organisations%20could%20help%20reduce%2C%20control%20or%20eradicate%20obstetric%20violence%20and%20misogyny%20in%20birth%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWomen%20feeling%20safe%20and%20cared%20for%20during%20their%20pregnancy%20will%20result%20in%20better%20maternal%20and%20child%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20a%20flourishing%20care%20regime%20that%20prioritises%20women%E2%80%99s%20concerns%2C%20pain%20management%20and%20dignity%20requires%20that%20women%20are%20given%20the%20right%20to%20participate%20in%20decisions%20concerning%20their%20labour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EDr.%20Vijayetta%20Sharma%20is%20Associate%20Professor%20of%20Public%20Policy%20at%20Manav%20Rachna%20International%20Institute%20of%20Research%20and%20Studies.%20She%20has%20been%20a%20Post-doctoral%20Research%20Fellow%20at%20Indian%20School%20of%20Business%20(ISB).%20Her%20research%20areas%20are%20maternal%20and%20child%20health%2C%20social%20security%2C%20and%20governance.%20She%20specialises%20in%20public%20policy%20and%20management%20and%20has%20worked%20in%20management%20courses%20with%20academicians%20across%20the%20globe.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOriginally%20published%20under%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcreativecommons.org%2Flicenses%2Fby%2F4.0%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ECreative%20Commons%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0by%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F360info.org%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E360info%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%E2%84%A2.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708674687000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F23131855%2FScreenshot-2024-02-23-at-1.18.15%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fmedical-misogyny-we-need-to-talk-about-obstetric-violence