omes%2Farticleshow%2F107926743.cms%23%3A~%3Atext%3DKuki%2520families%2520allege%2520illegal%2520occupation%2CImphal%2520city%2520to%2520Kangpokpi%2520district.%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Times%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChurch%20official%20S.%20Prim%20Vaiphei%2C%20one%20of%20the%20people%20evacuated%2C%20told%20the%20newspaper%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20illegal%20occupation%20of%20our%20houses%20is%20happening%20under%20the%20noses%20of%20Imphal%20East%20district%20administration%20and%20central%20security%20forces.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVaiphei%20said%20this%20was%20a%20violation%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20order%20telling%20the%20authorities%20to%20safeguard%20the%20properties%20of%20those%20displaced%20due%20to%20the%20ethnic%20violence%20that%20began%20on%20May%203.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fmanipur-new-lambulances-last-kuki-families%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20last%20Kuki%20families%20who%20remained%20in%20Imphal%2C%20in%20the%20New%20Lambulane%20area%2C%20had%20accused%20the%20authorities%20of%20forcibly%20evacuating%20them%20on%20September%202%20last%20year.%20A%20total%20of%2024%20individuals%20from%20the%20Kuki%20community%20were%20evacuated%20from%20New%20Lambulane%20on%20that%20day%2C%20including%20infants%20and%20people%20in%20need%20of%20regular%20hospital%20checkups.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImphal%20East%20DSP%20K.%20Meghachandra%20Singh%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Times%20of%20India%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethat%20the%20police%20had%20taken%20steps%20to%20stop%20the%20takeover%20of%20properties%20after%20%E2%80%9Creceiving%20inputs%20about%20some%20people%20trying%20to%20take%20over%20some%20abandoned%20houses%20in%20New%20Lambulane%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20people%20say%20they%20have%20been%20living%20in%20relief%20camps%20and%20want%20to%20shift%20to%20better%20places%20such%20as%20abandoned%20houses.%20We%